,"bulletinDateSort":143,"citedRangeSort":334,"languageSort":337,"materialSort":231,"typeSort":15},"ISic000781","Funerary inscription of Aurelius Samohil",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":229},"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":231,"ana":232,"type":25,"subtype":233,"resp":28,"ref":29},"Coarse-grained, banded, white marble, likely Aphrodisian, Parian-2, Parian-3, Parian-4, Proconnesian, Thasian-3. Digital microscopy: heteroblastic fabric (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Aphrodisian #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Parian-2 #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Parian-3 #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Parian-4 #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Proconnesian #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.dolomitic_marble.Thasian-3",[234,235,236,237,238,239],"Aphrodisian","Parian-2","Parian-3","Parian-4","Proconnesian","Thasian-3",{"ana":38},{"layout":242},{"p":243,"rs":244,"damage":245},"A single line of Hebrew is followed by 14 lines of Latin; the Latin text observes a more or less regular left margin, irregular on the right. The lower right and left corners contain small incised menorahs, with the last line of text between them consisting simply of 'overspill' from the preceding line, offset towards the right.",{"_":43,"ana":44,"ref":45},{"ana":246},"#text_condition.legible",{"lettering":248,"dimensions":249},"Letters generally neatly and regularly cut, with basic serifs on the long strokes. B is somewhat irregular in fomration, sometimes with equal loops, sometimes with smaller upper loop; C is large and open; E is narrow, with three short equal horizontal strokes; G has distinctive form of small C with a tail descending to lower right; M is formed of four equal diagonal strokes; P has a somewhat elongated frequently (but not always) closed loop, but some instances have a wide horizaontal foot also; Q is closed with a trailing tail;  R is usually closed, with a tail usually straight and extended but finishing above the line; S is frequently oversize. The two menorahs at the foot of the inscription are 15 mm and 23 mm (the left is incomplete).",[250,254,260],{"type":52,"l":170,"from":54,"to":54,"h":251,"unit":57,"atLeast":252,"atMost":253},"7-15","7","15",{"type":52,"l":255,"from":63,"to":256,"h":257,"unit":57,"atLeast":258,"atMost":259},"Lines 2-15","line15","9-19","9","19",{"type":61,"l":62,"from":54,"to":63,"h":261,"unit":57},"not measured",{"_":263,"notBefore":264,"notAfter":264,"evidence":265},"383 CE",383,"internal-date",[267,270],{"_":268,"type":71,"ref":269,"region":73},"Catina","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270",{"_":271,"type":76,"ref":272,"region":73},"Catania","http://sws.geonames.org/2525068",[274],[275,276],37.49223,15.07041,[278,279],37.505019,15.088801,{"_":281,"role":89,"ref":282},"Museo Civico di Catania","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018",{"_":284,"type":93},"540",{"_":286,"mainLang":287,"otherLangs":288,"languages":289},"Latin and Hebrew","la","heb",[290,291],"Latin","Hebrew","175684",{"n":100,"url":294,"height":295,"width":296,"desc":297,"surfaceType":105},"ISic000781_tiled.tif","2856px","4272px","Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, 2017-05-11",[299,302],{"atLeast":300,"atMost":301},7,15,{"atLeast":303,"atMost":304},9,19,[112,111,111,306,307,308,309,310,311,312,313,116],"Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Libertini, 1929, Epigrafe giudaico-latina rinvenuta in Catania","Frey, 1936-1952, CIJ","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Manganaro, 1993, Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.","Noy, 1993, Jewish inscriptions of Western Europe","Grüll, 2000, \" Conquerors, Patriarchs and the Law of the Lord\". Interpretation of a late antique Je